# Mobile-native UI

This is a native Expo app, not a web/PWA port. Prefer platform conventions over HTML/CSS idioms.

## Touch targets

- Prefer **48dp** control heights; never ship below **44pt** without `hitSlop`.
- Use shared `hitSlop` from `@/theme` on `Button`, `IconButton`, list/chip presses, and icon-only controls.
- Do not use mouse-sized 36–40 heights as defaults.

## Typography

- Body **16**, secondary **14**, caption/helper/badge/tab labels **12** (never below 11).
- Section titles: h1 **28**, h2 **22**, h3 **20**.
- Button labels and input/label text **16**.

## Page chrome

- Tab labels (or a stack header) identify the screen. Do **not** add full-width teal page-title banners or `Screen title=` / `subtitle=`.
- Use `SectionHeader` only for in-content section labels, not to restate the route name.

## Links

- Tappable text uses color + weight (optional chevron). Never `textDecorationLine: 'underline'` for links.

## Radii

- Use the token scale (`sm` 8 / `md` 12 / `lg` 16). Avoid 4–6px “admin panel” corners.

## Input focus

- Keep the same `borderWidth` on focus; change `borderColor` (or a light fill) only. No CSS-style 1→2px focus outlines.
